Independent work with IR literature in agreement with the instructor.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course introduces the students to the current state of IR as a discipline. It discusses the key practical and theoretical concerns that define the discipline, the main theoretical debates, and the key concepts that organise the disciplinary field.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the students: 1) understand the disciplinary logic of IR and its evolution since the beginning of the twentieth century; 2) understand the key dividing lines between the rationalist and constructivist approaches in contemporary IR and brings out its strengths and weaknesses; 3) argue how and why IR theories differ in their approach to the key concepts that shape the disciplinary field; 4) demonstrate their critical reading skills; 5) use scholarly concepts and theories for their research.
